Add `opentelemetry-instrumentation-sagemaker`, instrumenting the AWS SageMaker
runtime (`sagemaker-runtime` client's `invoke_endpoint`) via `boto3`/`botocore`.
Because `invoke_endpoint` payloads are opaque, model-specific bytes, the emitted
standard GenAI semantic conventions (`gen_ai.*`) are intentionally thin:
`gen_ai.provider.name` (`aws.sagemaker`), `gen_ai.operation.name`, and
`gen_ai.request.model` (the SageMaker endpoint name). Telemetry is emitted via
`opentelemetry-util-genai` and requires
`OTEL_SEMCONV_STABILITY_OPT_IN=gen_ai_latest_experimental`.
